ONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Crow</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>2/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>9:37:44 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I need your advice!!!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">PLEASE ... I'm so confused!! Ok, here is the deal. I have enough shards and stuff to get a piece of med shadow armor. I already have pre-patch med shadow amuli legs and if I go to the amuli vendor I should get a med amuli shadow top but post patch. Post patch means the al is a little lower but you can put a major stone in it for elemental protection. Now, do I go for the amuli top or wait until I can get the greater amuli top? I'm proabably 5 cracked and several shadow frags away from getting it. On the other hand...I could save all the items until I have 1.5 scint gems and probably trade for a mattie robe. So, mattie robe, greater top, med top, or start over in a completely different form of armor? What would you do?</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bforgottentruthforeignlegion.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dia>Dia</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>2/12/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10:16:00 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic&index=1><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: I need your advice!!!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">It's very difficult to give you an advice on this. When you will give the gem to the armour maker, will he recognize your old shadow pants and give you the new top? I haven't read anything on this. Assuming that he does, I would take the armor right away. It will be al 120, not bad. The greater one is al 150 for 2 times the gems!<br>
I now know that the armor has no effects against magic spells. The only things that reduces damage from a magic spell are life protections. So I wouldn't take the matti robe with its al 60.<br>
I would take the acid stone for the armor (the worst attacks come from acid) and still get above average protection against fire and frost. Or the fire stone and get above for acid and lightning.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>2/12/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>5:11:15 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=487.topic&index=2><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: I need your advice!!!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Hmmm, Dia's advice makes a lot of sense to me. Unless you really have your heart set on getting the greater top, then go for it! Personally, I'd go for the armor over the robe, it's so much more stylish!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
